  "description": {
    "en-US": "Travel phrases for Germany with audio, built for DB train travel, S-Bahn and U-Bahn transfers, hotel check-ins, bakeries, and everyday service questions.",
    "zh-CN": "德国旅行短语卡，围绕 DB 火车、S-Bahn 与 U-Bahn、酒店入住、面包店和日常服务沟通等高频场景整理。"
  },
  "intro": {
    "en-US": "Built for Germany trips where DB platforms, local transit, hotel check-ins, bakery counters, and museum days come one after another. These cards help when you need short German for ticket questions, platform changes, cash or card checks, or direct but polite service requests.",
    "zh-CN": "这套德国短语适合那种 DB 站台、本地交通、酒店前台、面包店和博物馆会连续出现的旅行节奏。遇到要问车票、站台变更、现金还是刷卡，或者提出简短但礼貌的服务请求时，短语卡会很有帮助。"
  },
  "teaser": {
    "en-US": "Built for Germany DB travel, S-Bahn and U-Bahn transfers, bakeries, and hotel or museum-day logistics.",
    "zh-CN": "适合德国 DB、S-Bahn 与 U-Bahn、面包店，以及酒店和博物馆行程沟通。"
  },
  "travelTips": {
    "en-US": [
      "Keep transport phrases ready for DB delays, platform changes, and S-Bahn or U-Bahn directions because those details change quickly.",
      "Germany is still mixed on card acceptance, so cash and payment phrases are worth keeping handy even in big cities.",
      "Bakery and cafe counters move fast, and a short German request is useful for takeaway, table water, or asking what is included."
    ],
    "zh-CN": [
      "DB 延误、站台变更，以及 S-Bahn 或 U-Bahn 方向确认都很常见，交通短语最好提前备好。",
      "德国很多地方在支付方式上仍然比较混合，所以现金和刷卡相关短语值得一直放在手边。",
      "面包店和咖啡馆柜台节奏很快，想要外带、要一杯水，或者确认包含什么内容时，简短德语会很有用。"
    ]
  },
  "highlights": {
    "en-US": [
      "DB trains, cash questions, and bakery stops",
      "S-Bahn, U-Bahn, and platform changes",
      "Hotels, museums, and direct service requests"
    ],
    "zh-CN": [
      "DB、现金支付与面包店沟通",
      "S-Bahn、U-Bahn 与站台变更",
      "酒店、博物馆与简短服务请求"
    ]
  },
