  "faq": [
    {
      "question": {
        "en-US": "Which phrase groups matter most for a first Germany itinerary?",
        "zh-CN": "第一次去德国旅行，最该先准备哪几组短语？"
      },
      "answer": {
        "en-US": "Start with transport, hotel, and dining. That covers DB, local transit, check-in, bakeries, and most first-day logistics in Germany.",
        "zh-CN": "建议先看交通、酒店和餐饮三组，基本就能覆盖 DB、本地交通、入住办理、面包店，以及德国第一天的大多数安排。"
      }
    },
    {
      "question": {
        "en-US": "Why are payment phrases still useful in Germany?",
        "zh-CN": "为什么在德国旅行时，支付类短语仍然很有用？"
      },
      "answer": {
        "en-US": "Because some places still prefer cash or have minimum card rules. A short phrase can save time when you want to know how to pay before ordering.",
        "zh-CN": "因为一些地方仍然偏好现金，或者会有刷卡门槛。提前问清楚怎么支付，往往能帮你省掉很多来回确认。"
      }
    }
  ]
